olive oil
½ Brown Onion
1 packet beef strips
½ tbs honey
¼ tsp salt
2 radish
1 tomato
6 Mini Flour Tortillas
1 packet Dill & Parsley Mayonnaise
1 bag Mixed Leaves
2 tbs vinegar (white  wine or rice wine)
1 sachet Berbere seasoning

• Thinly slice onion (see ingredients).
• In a small bowl, combine the vinegar and a good pinch of salt and sugar.
Scrunch sliced onion in your hands, then add it to pickling liquid with just
enough water to cover onion. Set aside.

• While the onion is pickling, combine Berbere seasoning, the honey, a
drizzle of olive oil and the salt in a medium bowl. Season with pepper, then
add beef strips. Toss to coat and set aside.
• Thinly slice radish and tomato.
• In a second medium bowl, combine radish, tomato and a drizzle of olive
oil. Season and set aside.

• Heat a large frying pan over high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. When oil is
hot, cook beef strips in batches, tossing, until browned and cooked through
1-2 minutes. Transfer to a plate.
• Meanwhile, microwave mini flour tortillas on a plate for 10 second bursts,
until warmed through.

TIP: Cooking the meat in batches over a high heat helps it stay tender.

• Drain pickled onion.
• Spread tortillas with dill & parsley mayonnaise, then top with radish salad,
mixed leaves and shawarma beef.
• Garnish with pickled onion to serve. Enjoy!